[h3 
	" Dr. Doom's Castle
	$LF
]h3
[p 
	"This stage was the first one to be done for two reasons; it's a really small stage and the boss don't need to be killed, just half of his life bar must be drained away to receive my first gem.
	$LF
]p
[h4 
	" Boss: Dr. Doom
	$LF
]h4
[p 
	"The strategy to beat Dr. Doom is pretty simple; never let him do his flying attacks and only knock him down when his green life bar is gone.
	$LF
]p
[h4 
	" Time Gem
	$LF
]h4
[p 
	"This gem is supposed to make the hero move twice as quick, but it's not true; Wolverine normal walking speed is 144, using the Time Gem it goes to 208.
	$LF
]p
[h3 
	" Alaska
	$LF
]h3
[p 
	"This stage is one of the easier stages for Wolverine or Spider-Man thanks to their natural abilities, but Wolverine was chosen due to his slightly faster walking speed, increased using the Time Gem.
	$LF
]p
[h4 
	" Boss: Evil Sasquatch
	$LF
]h4
[p 
	"To keep his combo, Wolverine must hit the boss twice then turn around and waste one hit, but if he is falling off of a ledge, turning around makes him land again on that ledge so he can start his two hit combo again.
	$LF
]p
[h4 
	" Reality Gem
	$LF
]h4
[p 
	"A rather useless gem to use on a TAS, it allows the hero to see invisible items.
	$LF
]p
[h3 
	" Boston Aquarium
	$LF
]h3
[p 
	"Here in this stage you will need a character that can perform air combos, Iron Man and Captain America are the only ones that can do so. The faster character was chosen; Iron Man. The Time Gem doesn't increase the speed of special moves like the Iron Rocket Torpedo, but since there's some cut scenes where the hero walks atomatically, it was used again to save some time.
	$LF
]p
[h4 
	" Boss: Evil Irom Man (x2)
	$LF
]h4
[p 
	"At first glance it may seem unfair to fight two bosses at the same time, but it soon proves to be one of the easier boss fights of the game. Since they share the same energy bar, it's not beneficial to hit them at the same time as it will draw the same amount of energy regardless.
	$LF
]p
[h3 
	" Amazon
	$LF
]h3
[p 
	"This stage is pretty straight forward, beat your way through until you reach the alarm that sets off the evil Pucks. The recommendable character to use in this stage is Spider Man, but he is one of the slowest heroes of the game, so it's up to Iron Man again.
	$LF
]p
[h4 
	" Boss: Evil Wolverine
	$LF
]h4
[p 
	"The strategy to defeat Evil Wolverine is a mix between Dr. Doom and Evil Sasquatch's boss fights, abuse the fall off of a ledge trick and only knock him down when his life bar is gone.
	$LF
]p
[h3 
	" Spaceship
	$LF
]h3
[p 
	"There's a really stupid bug if you drop through the hatch too fast; you'll trigger the opening of the hatch, but you'll also land on the right ledge while the hatch closes, then you're stuck. 
	$LF
]p
[h4 
	" Boss: Magus
	$LF
]h4
[p 
	"This boss fight may be the most boring fight of the run, but there's a reason for the strategy used; Magus will teleport just like Akuma from time to time, even worse is that he is totally invincible when doing so.
	$LF
]p
[h4 
	" Power Gem
	$LF
]h4
[p 
	"The most useful gem of the game, the gem bestows Hulk's attack power to all the other characters. Obviously, Hulk will not benefit from it.
